caption: Mouthwatering tapas that are carefully done and well presented. I highly recommend.

We have been here several times and have always been on the patio but tonight we choose to move indoors. We just had a couple of snacks and dessert which were very delicious. We had the street corn, the roasted beets and the berry cobbler. The berry cobbler was scrumptious and you need to try this when visiting!
Always such an amazing experience. Food, service, atmosphere - can't get much better. Chef Taylor is a mastermind in the culinary world - and Don the server is awesome.

As much as I want to like this place I cannot.  The food is mediocre at best but the worst part is, you are likely to be forgotten.  Perhaps it's a result of the shots and drinks the staff enjoy throughout the night that impairs them to the point that they are unaware of your presence.  Or perhaps it's the complacency that seems to have settled upon them.  The bar staff is on point.  They make great drinks and are very engaged.  The problem is the food and the leadership.  It is clear that if you are dining, you are a far second to the fun the staff wants to have!  Do yourself a favor and walk 15 yards to Citizen Soul.  You will be well taken care of!  The two stars is solely reflective of the cocktails and the bar staff.  Otherwise I would have given Holmes a 1 star or lower,
When I say I love the brussel sprouts I absolutely love the brussel sprouts...I got them 3 days in a row
This place is amazing! Deliciously fresh food, amazing wine, and excellent service!
Very nice place ,not crowded at all. Not a big menu but it was tasty.

Although the service and atmosphere was outstanding yhe food wasn't as good.  The corn dish was excellent and the carrot dish had a nice sauce but don't expect orange carrots.  The hamburger was a bit dry.  Even with all that the service is what got the 3 stars...maybe we just picked the wrong things.
Always delicious! The Octopus and Brussel Sprouts never fail. Super friendly staff!

We sat on the patio last weekend and not only was the food enjoyable (we has the Cacio e Pepe, carrots, and brussel sprouts), plus a few of their signature cocktails, but service was the perfect balance of taking care of us and also social distancing. Highly recommend!
Great food and great bartenders.... cozy!

Very meh. The short ribs were so full of fat that I spent my entire meal doing surgery on them trying to find anything that qualifies as meat. Would have been great if our waiter had checked back even once to refill our beverages.

Had friends in town over the weekend and decided to go to Holmes for a nice dinner outside. We were told the patio was sat on a first-come, first-serve basis. We enjoyed drinks at the bar and waited over 90 minutes for a table to open (although there were empty tables everywhere). Normally, I’d understand that those empty tables likely belonged to other reservations, however, this wasn’t the case given we were advised they didn’t accept reservations for outside. When finally sat, it took another 20 minutes to get greeted from our server. Although the food was pretty good, the service was awful. There were 6 of us and our check came at the end and our server made us separate our own check with pen and paper. What a joke! There are far too many other quality restaurants in the neighborhood to return here. Huge disappointment.
Party of 10 with guaranteed gratuity = terrible service.  Food was good service sucked.

Amazing service, I can not for the life of me remember the gals name who has been my server/bartender twice...  She has been over the top amazing and super friendly.  The food and drinks are amazing here as well, the tomato salad followed by the NY Strip (upon her rec.) was the perfect combo!
Delicious! Brussel sprouts, short ribs, homemade pasta, and strawberry cobbler! Wow! Could not have been better!
Tasty and creative

Honestly terrible experience. Other than my drink which was delicious & our server who was very nice & wonderful, the food was just awful. We got the short ribs as an appetizer which was so overcooked, tough & chewy that we had to ask for steak knives to cut it & eventually gave up & tried using our hands & teeth to gnaw it off the bone. More than half of the plate was the bone too & it was all really charred & not enjoyable at all.  We then decided to order the grilled sourdough with whipped ricotta because we’ve had a similar appetizer at other restaurants & loved it & figured it would hold us over until the entrees came since the first appetizer was so bad. The bread was so terrible that we had to send it back (like we should have with the short rib). The bread was so charred that it tasted burnt (even the server said that’s not the first complaint she’s heard about it & she herself agrees!), it was served with a whipped ricotta with dill & chives - but so many that it was incredibly overpowering & we were practically chewing on herbs & aromatics... then beside that was a bunch of raw vegetables. Yes raw. Raw carrots, broccoli & cherry tomatoes that were all cold like they were just pulled from the fridge - zero flavor.  Then our entrees came. He got the Chicken sandwich & I got the salmon. The chicken sandwich came soaked in buffalo sauce & ranch & served on Texas toast & he said it was absolutely awful (I didn’t want to try it). I got the salmon, which itself was delicious (my husband agreed) & cooked perfectly, but the glaze on top of it was so overpowering that it was hard to enjoy the salmon. It was served with a mixture of plain steamed shredded carrots, tiny broccoli pieces & cabbage.  Both of our stomachs have been hurting & upset ever since we left a few hours ago too. I was so bummed because it had good reviews online & it was one of the only remaining restaurants in the downtown Alpharetta area that we’ve yet to try, but honestly we’re sad we wasted $90 on this dinner for our first date night out without our baby since Covid. Such a disappointment but hopefully this saved you from a terrible experience as well!

Plenty of options for everyone. The watermelon salad was my favorite. Small plates and portions. Great for sharing. The drinks are also good. Nice outdoor patio. Plenty of social distancing and an amazingly friendly staff.
Great place with phenomenal chicken paillard and LA style short ribs
Great Cheesburger!
Great food, great selection of liquors, great bartenders. Always enjoy dining here

Service was excellent but the food not so much.  We had the salmon that was good and an order of brussel sprouts.  Stay away from the short ribs ..they were flat greasey slabs of awful.  Not at all whaty would think of as beautiful tender p  of meat
Great hangout for adults with an even better staff!

Honestly, I don't get the low ratings. I've been here twice and sat at the bar both times. The bar is refreshingly quaint and charming. The bartenders are so friendly. I just love the Weight of Sound drink.  I had a plate of crispy potatoes because I needed a snack. They lived up to the name. They arrived on a bed of aioli sauce, which goes so well with it. Enjoyed every bite of that.  Restaurant Holmes is one of my favorite restaurants in the Alpharetta City Center space. Looking forward to trying their full menu sometime.
Excellent bartender skills!
Food good but drinks way to expensive for their tiny size ..
Always quality food, talented team members taking excellent care of every detail.
We will likely give it another try, but the service was slow and that was a less than stellar beginning.  The food was OK, but lacked flavor.  Maybe an off night in the kitchen.
Okay so for a holiday--like Valentines Day-- this restaurant is packed. I'm going to try again. If its this packed, then clearly there is something good here. Try it!
A truly wonderful experience. You will absolutely get what you pay for. The cocktails were delicious and food was excellent.

One of our new favorites. The place has a cool vibe while also maintaining a nice feel of elegance. The staff is friendly, and on top of their game. They can dive into each of the plates and genuinely feel like they love the food as much as we do. Now the food will blow your mind. Its pretty reasonably priced for the quality that you get. They change the menu up often which always brings new flavors to the classic dishes. Get the octopus, even if you havent liked it from other places, this octopus is like nothing ive had before.
Incredible food and wonderful service. Thanks for the great experience David, we will definitely be back soon.
Amazing experience. Don was a fantastic knowledgeable entertaining server! Burger was delicious and the steak and fries was fresh and juicy! Will always come back
A real quality and crafted meal; very attentive staff
Excellent wine suggestions. The sea bass was excellent and sides were delicious. Lovely place!!

We dined at Holmes right before Thanksgiving . I had a great Grouper fillet, perfectly cooked with fresh vegetables. My wife and mother in law both got short ribs, which were very good.  We finished with desert. Very good time. Excellent food and great service by the whole staff.

Came here over the weekend for late lunch, service was a little slow but food was decent, not great.  I like my crispy cod sandwich but my husband’s burger was on the saltier side, the burger had too much salt in the meat patty.  We both enjoyed the mushroom bread toast tho.
Nice atmosphere, cozy interior that doesn't feel cramped but is minimalistic. Small plate menu style, wide range of selections. Would recommend.

Well, what food we got tasted good but WAAAAAY over priced. On the lunch menu, 8 leafs of arugula, two small beets, and a clementine will cost you $12. My grouper sandwich was good but had a slice of processed Kraft Singles American Cheese (unmelted) on top for the low low price of $16. I wish I'd taken a picture. It was surreal.  Maybe the dinner menu is better? This was disappointing given the number of positive reviews.

Great tasting tapas and drinks! We all had a good time. I do think the mixed drinks are a little overpriced and some of the tapas as well! Excellent quality foods and fantastic customer service all around!
Great place amazing food
Ok good, nothing very special or unique.
Not recommending to others - didn't like food.

Amazing spot. Every dish was fantastic. Seriously, all 6 we had were phenomenal. Crispy octopus was perfectly cooked with extraordinary mint, garlic aioli and honey combination. House-made CeCe e Pepe was simple in appearance, but chewy texture and fresh parmesan flavor were surprisingly impressive. Ribeye with jalapeno aioli was deliciously savory, and who doesn't love a well seasoned waffle fry?! Duck with roasted root vegetables in creamy mashed potatoes and gravy was succulent and delectable. Desserts were a flawless finish. Apple toffee cake with homemade vanilla soft serve was guiltily sublime. The chocolate dome filled with black forest mousse atopped with raspberry drizzle was exquisite. Great service and gorgeous atmosphere. Definitely a new fave.
Very good ambience.. lovely putside sitting .. good food and lot of drink options..must visit
Awesome bar! Bartenders are not only knowledgeable, but friendly. Fantastic bar culture with a great wine and cocktail menu.
Hands down the best place to try out the crafty cocktails!! The food is impeccable and always mixing it up through the seasons! One of our favorites!

The food is top notch and always changing. The pasta is amazing, no matter what. The service is knowledgeable and the bartenders are very welcoming. It's a kind of small restaurant, if you have a big party call ahead!
Family
Great service. Perfect portion size. Food was wonderful. Grouper so good. Excellent cheese plate. Good rum selection! Even had amazing tenders for the kiddo.
Great little bar. Leo the bartender did an awesome job very professional!

Four of us dined here for lunch. Service and surroundings are quite pleasant, however, the kids chicken ‘tenders’ were made of chicken thigh (no mention of this in the menu) complete with all the fatty bits (I wouldn’t eat that let alone my 8yr old) so we had to order another dish instead and wait for that to come out. A separate dish, the fish sandwich, was actually served raw (not cooked in the middle at all). It was actually quite tasty once it had been sent back to the kitchen and cooked properly but ya know, food 101...  Nothing taken off our bill for the inconvenience. But really the manager should have come out and had a quiet word after the raw fish incident. So unfortunately a disappointing experience for us which is a shame as it’s a nice place and like what they’ve done with the old house.

Not a good experience!  It took a while for the food to come, and the food was served item by item, not all together like a typical meal. We had six people in our party. We ordered everything at the same time, but we received two sides first and then one entree 10 or so minutes later. The sides were cold before we received even one entree. Wait staff was pleasant, but for the cost, I would not go there again.
Liked the farm to table choices.
Killer cocktails and the fried chicken sandwich is amazing
Menu has something for everyone. Great octopus dish and great drinks!
Wow!  The food was amazing but just wait for dessert!!!
Great crispy octopus tail! Creative cocktails and the food was tasty
Awesome food, drinks and company. Octopus and grouper sandwich done right! Go now!

This was our first time to visit Holmes, I was a little disappointed.  My son and daughter-in-law were flying back to Seattle later and both sides of the family decided to all have lunch together, 7 people in all.  The table we were seated at was al little cramped, but we had the room to ourselves so it wasn't loud. It seemed to take a long time to get service (my wife kept trying to wave someone down), eventually our daughter-in-law's mother got up and asked the fellow who seemed to be attending to the bar (he wasn't behind the bar, but it looked like he worked there) if we could get someone to take our orders.  After ordering, the food didn't take long to arrive, about normal wait time. It tasted good, it wasn't bad. But for the price, it seemed rather ordinary and small portioned.  I had the BLT. It was bood bread, toasted with a lot of butter/oil. There wasn't a terrific amount of bacon, lettuce, or tomato. But it did have enough sauce to soak through the thick bread and start to soften it. The sandwich was mostly bread and oil.  There were 7 of us for lunch. One of us ordered a beer. A few had some cold brew coffe. We each had a sandwich or salad. The bill came to about $155, with tip it totaled about $185.  Give the large number of really terrific resturants in the area, and for this price, we'll keep going to our regular places and try the occasional new places.

What a fantastic meal.  We were there on Friday night.  I don't know who's back there cooking but we were SO happy!  We had the Grouper and Steelhead Trout.  Cocktails and service we on point.  Thank guys for a lovely meal.
I love the concept and I've had great experiences here before. Tonight execution was just ok.
Great seasonal drinks and menu. Great staff and incredibly pup friendly on the patio.
Great drinks, but the food is extremely overpriced and under-portioned. There is no reason to hit 3 figures on a bill and still leave hungry.
Good choices of tapas . Always well made with some oil or spice that makes it different than other places.  Service is always good.
Amazing drinks, amazing food set in historic building with perfect service. You’ll be shocked that EVERYTHING is your new favorite.
Don't go with a group of more than 4 people, they do not like groups.
Servers were fun and friendly. Food was delicious.

This restaurant was so accommodating and made my grandfather's 89th birthday a blast! The food was superb and the owner is one of the nicest guys I've met. All of the staff greet you and talk to you with a smile like you're already friends.  Without hesitation we were able to get my girlfriend something to eat as well. Her list of things she's not allergic to is a smaller list. Restaurant Holmes made her be able to enjoy the evening and have something delicious to eat as well.  This place is a shining example of how a family-run restaurant should feel. It's like you're stepping into their home instead of into a restaurant.
Great selection of different types of food which are done wonderfully.  Bar is one of the best in the area.  Very good thing going on here.
Great dining experience!
Love this place! Beautiful space and the bartenders are great.
After being seated, we waited around 25 minutes, and no one came to our table to serve water, greet, or acknowledge us. Even with attempts to get someone’s attention. So we left.
Great atmosphere, food and service
Yummy food and chill environment.
Great food and excellent service
Everything we had was delicious!

Not a typical restaurant I expected. Did not seem at have lot of selection.Food was not that good and nothing memorable.  Brocolli was fried and was not expecting that. Bread was burnt and replaced w non burnt bread, however burnt taste still remained. Had the shrimp fettuccini and short ribs. Short ribs also were cooked charred as well.

Portions were tiny for the price and even despite the size (where you'd expect quality) many of the dishes we had as a group were mediocre.  The pork belly was pretty good, but the ravioli, chicken, cauliflower, kalimari, shrimp were all nothing special.  The environment here is nice though, and based on reactions from a subset of our group, it helps with perception of the food.  About 70% of us thought it was overpriced and trying to be fancy but tasted meh, but the other 30% were swept into the appearance and atmosphere and thought the food was impressive.  So it's probably as simple as if you like ritzy stuff and feel better paying more money, you'll probably like this place, otherwise avoid.
Amazing fresh food! By far the best service and food I have had in a while. Absolutely loved the ravioli!
ok
Great new place to come to the neighborhood who is needed for that area. Drinks are good and so was the octopus

Our first experience was excellent and food was good.  However our recent experience was not good at all.  We have had better food and presentation of food in a dinner.  Wait staff was friendly and helpful but that’s were it ended.  We will not go back!

Great small plates galore tapas. The small beer pour?... is 17oz in a 20oz glass fyi. They did have a great menu for both small plates and larger portions as well. If you're getting dessert strongly recommend the strawberry cobbler.

My husband and I went with friends of Saturday evening and was able to right in. They were welcoming and friendly as soon as we arrived. The wait staff was exceptional and also very knowledge!! The food and drinks were superb. We will definitely be back.👏👏👏

We went there on a Monday and the place was spectacular. From the crafted cocktails to the small plates, it was a lovely dinner date with my hubby. The plates are great to share with two people and the price is spot on for what they offer. We can't wait to return to see what the new seasons bring to the menu!
Sat at the bar for just one drink but loved it. Wished we could've stayed longer. The staff were very friendly and the setting is beautiful.
Terrible service, terrible food, long wait for food. However was holiday weekend. Won't go back

Fancy restaurant,very crowded, friendly staff but the food couldn't convince me. Funny combinations, which are not always a succes. I had the " not so small " plate,like it's written on the menu,  but I was supprised how small it really was. The shrimps Came in peal but I had more empty peals.
I really liked it.  Was not expecting tappas here.  They know how to make a strong drink.  I'll be back!!! :-)
I like that they offer variety of menu items in tapas style. Ser ice was great. The outdoor seating is refreshing

Ordered the cauliflower and asparagus which where both tasty but also heavy. We ordered veggies to eat lite and lean but instead it was cheesy and oily.  The salads were on point and delicious.  The ambience was cool and it was convenient to downtown.  Lastly our service was quick and attentive but the really bad breath made that experience obviously awkward. The kind were you can smell it 5 ft away and gag. How do you tell your waiter to get a mint or brush their teeth?
Awesome flavor for each dish

Service was great and food was so yummy! The noise level is really loud but it made it part of the experience. The pork belly was to die for! The korean bbq  broccoli I think was fried and had a drizzled korean bbq auce drizzled over it...it was oddly delishous! The spaghetti was more of a fancy mac and cheese with spaghetti noodles. I loved this but my hubby didn't as much. The cocktails were so delish!  Oh and the fruity pebbles icecream was genius! Huge hit and we will be back!
Really great little restaurant. Super creative menu and our server, Don I think was his name, was a true professional. Great experience.
Good food lively atmosphere.
Very good selection of food & drinks.  Service was excellent.  Will be back!
Nice relaxing atmosphere. Good food.

This restaurant is amazing! The yellowtail, broccoli appetizer, the fish, the martinis were all fantastic! The chef /owner Taylor came out and checked on us and even cut our fish for us. What a treat. Waiter was awesome. LOVE finding unique amazing restaurants like this. Highly recommend. Love!!!
I really enjoyed the food and atmosphere! The waitstaff was friendly and helpful. A great place to meet friends sit outside and hangout or eat dinner or both!!
Grilled cheese was fantastic, and great service!
Great food, individual needs happily net, great service too.

The caliber and flavors of these small plates are astronomically above the bar for your standard "tapas" affair. The drinks are amazing, the atmosphere is fun, the service is beyond top notch. It might be a bit crowded inside but it's worth it. The farm to table food is hands down some of the best I've had since moving to Georgia. This will be a new favorite for years to come.

This is a really cool restaurant right in the heart of the Alpharetta city center. We ordered o bunch of different things off the menu and they were all so different and delicious! The ambiance is great and the service awesome. It’s also very clean!! They also have a great drink menu. Definitely worth a try. You don’t get a bunch of food for your money but it’s a great place. Can’t wait to go back.
The restaurant is well put together! The staff is nice, and music is great! I had their Ravioli with baby potatoes!  Wish that had more options on the menu!
The place is nice but not the food
The food was great, nice wine list and our server was excellent, high energy, friendly.  Ambience was great too, moderately loud but not too much.  Will definitely return.
Great atmosphere.  The hummus toast is an awesome snack

Great service from Ashley, to great food in the patty melt, with grilled sourdough bread, crunch was amazing and the perfect bread to soak up the sauce...fried chicken sandwich also a can’t miss and don’t be afraid of the Korean BBQ sauce...a little spice in your life is ok!!!

Disappointing.  Nice atmosphere and a couple of interesting and delicious small plates did make their way to the table.  Broccoli was served cool with the sauces over it hot.  Ordered the lamb chops medium and was served lukewarm on the outside and “cold” on the inside chops that were prepared well done.  The only way I can logically understand  coming up with this result is pre-cooked food that has been reheated.  For the price this establishment is charging for the lamb chops that is a completely unacceptable practice.  Plate was sent back and was returned 8 minutes later cooked hot on the outside cool and purple in the middle (a very generous medium rare).  Way better options within walking distance and throughout Alpharetta
Always awesome. The food is fantastic, service is always great and the best porch situation in Alpharetta.
Great service, great cocktails, and outstanding food. Squash tortellini and the brussel sprouts were incredible.
Great service and food.
Delicious food, amazing staff, creative and tasty cocktails, and fun ambiance. We had such a great time!

Fun and interesting farm to table concept with ridiculously fresh ingredients and original recipes built to share mostly tapas style with a few mains for good measure. We enjoyed the sophisticated, yet upscale-casual atmosphere. The inspired cuisine changes with the season, so there's always something new and unusual. Dishes range from scallops with couscous, to Korean-style BBQ brussels (yum!), to exciting variations on more traditional faire like pappardelle bolognese. Highly recommended for adventurous foodies everywhere! 👌

Food is wonderful. Service is great. In my opinion currently the best restaurant in alpharetta. I have tried almost everything on the menu and have not had one bad item yet. The tapas style of service and the way the food is described on the menu can be a little overwhelming for some. I can promise order anything and you will not be disappointed. One of my current favorites are the carrots.
Quiant new restaurant. Pleasant atmosphere, and eclectic.
Good food. They put their own twist it.

You go here for taste, texture and ambiance!!!! I believe the quality matches price. If you think quantity should match the price, you may need to stick with your usual Taco Bell. This is a more sophisticated restaurant. Where you are there for the conversation and drinks while savoring the food. This will be a regular stop for my wife and I. If you are a “pig out” eater that likes to devour you food and go. This may not be your thing. Go read the one and two star reviews for this type. If you are sick of the same ole same ole. You MUST try Holmes. We were a party of four and ordered 8 small plates and 3 big plates to share so we could sample more. Everything was OUTSTANDING!!! Drinks too!!! We had them bring the food out slowly, one at a time. That way we could enjoy the conversation, drinks and sample the food slowly. We were there a little over two hours. It was as a blast!! You could close you eyes and just pick anything and it will be great!!!

Love this place. We did a little post holiday Sunday brunch and it was great. While they don't specifically have a brunch menu, many items we suitable for brunch style dining. They make a great bloddy Mary too! We will be back!

I really wanted to like this restaurant more honestly. The atmosphere is nice bordering on pretentious.  The location is perfect. The food was just ok. Some food was oversalted. Some things were not as described in the menu and contained things I couldn't eat which weren't listed on the menu. We had to ask for ice in our drinks.  The salad greens from Levity  were delicious but had been overdressed in food prep with salad dressing.  It is also too overpriced for the quality of the food.
Nice.  Regional food.  Not big entrees
Great drinks a interesting tapas.

Dinner for four in a quiet corner (pleasantly surprised that the dining room was so quiet on a busy Friday night).  It's simple food with high quality ingredients done well.  I see a lot of reviews saying that the food was good but the price was high and that's fair, but I still think it's a good value.  Food this fresh and local is a breath of fresh air, and we'll definitely be back.  Our waiter was excellent, manager checked in on us several times.  Drink prices are Midtown-high, but that's the new Alpharetta I guess.

Super nice and attentive service. Excellent Fried Chicken Korean sandwich. Patty melt was good. The crispy potatoes with herbed aioli were excellent!!!  The tea is horrible, no flavor... we had it in an Arnold Palmer and plain... horrible both times and the lemonade is $5 which is kind of ridiculous. Apparently they had some kind of special ingredient to it but it's definitely not worth $5... I'd rather have a glass of wine for a little more.  Would go back for the fried chicken sandwich and crispy potatoes.
Great staff, great drinks, damn good food
While we had a bit of a wait, service and food was exceptional.
Strong drinks, yummy food
Excellent food.  Try the pork chop - amazing.

An assortment of small plates of tasty food made to be shared. Most price are steap for the portion sizes but the food quality is great. Not a large bar menu and very few local options. Most food can be made vegetarian too.

Absolutely fantastic! Went there for lunch and service was great, food was so good I cannot wait to go back! The Pazole was so incredibly flavorful. The squash spaghetti was so amazing I wanted to lick the plate.

Stopped in for dinner 11/18 without reservation. Seated and greeted quickly. Two-top table indoors. Server was quick with drinks and attentive despite our arrival just before a massive rush and large party taking place.  The food tasted excellent.  First dish of potatoes was piping hot - excellent. Second dish of salmon was barely lukewarm. Hmm. Third dish, steak: cooked to proper medium rare, but again the dish was only lukewarm.  Given the tapas concept of food brought sequentially as it's prepared I didnt anticipate a cold food scenario occurring.  The staff was excellent. The food was delicious - but cold. Dang. I suspect the food runners were simply overwhelmed by the volume of a Sunday before Thanksgiving dinner rush.  I look forward to trying again in the future to update this rating.
Great service and food!
Awesome environment. Great Drinks. Super food.The staff is amazing.

Prices obscene for microscopic portions.  The quality of the food was very good, but the portion sizes are measured in bites.  5 bites of tortellini for $14.   Main entrees described as ample and large for 3-4 people but aren't enough to feed 1 person who has below average weight.   $14 for a glass of wine and $6 for a 12 oz can of beer.   Great tasting food at ridiculous prices.
Salads and deserts were great, the boiled salmon and hanger steak fair tasting over priced and a very small portion.
Such a cute place in downtown Alpharetta. The food was delicious and the wine selection was good.
Concept is weird. Everything is meant to share. Overpriced, wont be returning.

Great  Environment and great food! I have been there for both lunch and dinner and The menu is phenomenal! I highly recommend this place. It's small plates, but larger small plates,  and everything is made fresh daily.  The service was excellent and the staff is very welcoming from the time you open the door.
Always enjoy the unique farm to table selections the chef makes... .and the craft cocktails are wonderful.
Amazing restaurant with great service and food - decently priced for what you’re getting too.

Food was so tasty! The drinks were good too. Nice atmosphere. Chef came out to give us tips on the vegan options they can customize. Only slight criticism would be our sever seemed a bit off. She started out good but got a bit odd after a while. Definitely would go back though.
Decent quality and a great atmosphere and ambiance. Service is top notch.  Just pricey!  Grilled lettuce salad with minimal amount of chicken  is $20.00. Too much $$$

Great for drinks. The atmosphere is fun, cocktails taste great. However, skip dinner here and head somewhere else. Portions are very tiny and nothing to write home about. Most of my party left hungry despite ordering 3-4 plates per person.

Went tonight for dinner.  The atmosphere was nice and the server was delightful. We love eating out and frequent many restaurants around Atlanta.  The cocktails were good, but the food was over priced for  the portion size. The salad and brussel sprouts were drowning in sauce.  It was over powering.  We wish them the best, but will likely not return. #unfortunate
Great new restaurant. Friendly service, trendy atmosphere and delicious local food. The food came out very fast and there is plenty of parking in the parking garage.
Absolutely wonderful.  We hosted a baby shower in the private dining area.  It was a terrific setting and great food.  Our server Alaina did a fabulous job.
The food was good.  But they are all small plates.
Pricey but not extraordinary in taste. Not a bad experience, staff was great and nice atmosphere, but for me, probably a one time visit.

Great food, Great service and wonderful atmosphere.  Holmes came highly recommended and definitely did not disappoint.  The food was very flavorful and unique.  This was a wonderful place to celebrate a relaxed 10th year Wedding Anniversary.  Our server Georgia made the experience fun and was very knowledgeable about the food and super friendly.  This is a perfect place for a date or a celebration.
Great food and service, however, a little salty
Tasty dishes, comfortable atmosphere, very good wine

Probably the best restaurant in Alpharetta. Seeing a lot of reviews about the price/portion ratio. To be clear, no one at Holmes is ever deceptive about the price or the portions. Every time I’ve been to Holmes whoever has taken care of us has explained that they serve SMALL plates that come out as they are ready. What the dishes may lack in size they make up for in flavor, and I’ve never left unsatisfied with what I got for my money. I still have wet dreams about the charred octopus and the butternut squash ravioli. In addition to the kitchen being on point, the bar program is one of, if not THE most innovative in the area. I wish this place the absolute best of luck and can’t wait to watch them grow and continue to crush expectations. Big thanks to the whole team!

Great cocktails and nice patio. Love the small plates concept but the the selection is limited with the current menu being the summer menu. I expect seasonal changes and look forward to seeing their menu evolve. Great atmosphere for wine with nice selection,  cocktails and meeting with friends. No kids menu so definitely a date night spot. Service was on point. While the porch is awesome, I hope they will add shades as their Western exposure keeps the sun in your face and will make seeing that fancy pop-up TV difficult for afternoon games.

Just great addition to the main street Alpharetta.  Menu is small plates. Just the right touch for eating out casually. Service is spot on. Can't complain. Expectations are in line with decor, service and food.
Very good
It's pretty good.  A bit pricey. Just above average cuisine.

Really good! My wife and I enjoyed everything we had. The roasted potatoes were good, nice aioli with those. I had the seared tuna - was served differently than I've ever had it in a broth, so it wasn't cold or hot, but was certainly fresh. The pork belly was delicious. Georgia was our server and she was attentive, kind, and very knowledgeable about the menu.

The barley risotto with mushrooms, roasted beets with asparagus, and cauliflower were all really great! I’ve read some of the other reviews about portion size, and I get it, it’s not a huge portion, but you definitely get your money’s worth on the flavor, quality and creativity coming out of the kitchen! Come here for the joy of eating great food and you won’t be disappointed.

TL;DR: Great Service! Figuring out their lunch schedule a little bit still, food was definitely good - although a bit pricy for what it was. Would recommend  First the bad part: We went for lunch in a large group with a reservation and they struggled to get our food out to us in a timeley manner(45ish minutes).  Even then when it did come out some people's food came out a good 10-15 minutes before others did.  Good part: Credit where credit is due, they did a great job making sure we were taken care of in the meantime and also did a great job communicating with us about the hold up.  At the end of it they very generously insisted on comping the meal for our party since things hadn't gone to the manager's satisfaction. I did not talk to the manager directly, but was told by those who did talk to him/her that they were very pleasant and handled things excellently.  The Food: The food was pretty good and most people in our group really liked what they had. I can only speak for the Fried Chicken Sandwich and fries. It was certainly a pretty good meal, but if you're going for lunch expect to spend $20+ for an entree and side.  Not a problem for all, but in the realm of lunch meals it felt a bit expensive for what it was.  Atmosphere:  The atmosphere inside was really nice, it's in a renovated old house that they have done a very good job with.  The outside seating area also looked like a very nice place to sit and enjoy the small plates and wine they serve at dinner.  Overall Holmes was a good place to eat and while I would recommend that people try it I will only be going back very occasionally.

Coal Roasted Beets will make you a beet fan. First time in and I am looking forward to being back to try everything. It all looks super yummy and creative. Staff was super friendly. High end but not snobby. Instead of a dinner mint they offer Zotz, how fun!
Quickly became one of our favorite spots to hang out.  Cocktails are fantastic!  Bartenders are too much fun!
A wonderful overall experience, from food to drinks, but also deco, presentation & service! Will definitely come back
Excellent food and service.  A little pricey and  small servings.
Great food and great service!
Great people, amazing food with a top notch bar.

We chose to eat outside on the lovely porch.  All was fine until the flies found us.  I was looking forward to the squash dish and was disappointed that it had a bitter taste.  The prices were high for the amount of food you received.  Sorry to say I won't return.

Absolutely divine! The fresh ingredients make this restaurant spectacular! Chef Taylor Neary has put together an excellent menu with fresh ingredients that are flavorful and well put together.  A definite must come back to restaurant.
Luv it!

Our server was friendly and informative. She gave awesome recommendations and even went out of her way to fix our table that was wobbling slightly. We didn't even have to ask! Great food, great service.

Feels like a turist trap in the heart of Alpharetta. I've been living for a year now in Alpharetta and I've been to every restaurant or pub in downtown. Beeing a new open place I said to give it a try on a Friday evening. From the beginning I felt like in a turist trap. Waiters trying to push you getting the most expensive items on the menu promote them as local things (tell me where did you get your octopus and tuna localy :). After you order and you receive your diferent plates of food you realize that the quality is not what you expected for the amount of money you are paying. Unfortunately I just got good marketing and low quality. Disappointing...
In the area visiting and dined at Holmes for the first time. Enjoyed the plates we chose and the service we received. Best wishes for much success.

Food quality was great but the portions are extremely small. I understand the concept but $15 for small plates i except a bit more food on them. (See photo below) The hostess was nice but no smiles, the cocktail was great (Jack The Ripper - See photo below) and the atmosphere out in the patio was nice minus the mosquitoes. Our server was ok, we believe she forgot to add the last round of plates because everything we ordered was "cold plates" but she blamed the kitchen was backed up (25 minutes later) but nothing had to be really cooked and our neighbors plates all came out on time. That said, if you want to snack and have a few drinks this is your place, but not if you are hungry..

My date and I tried this restaurant tonight, we saw a beautiful menu and wanted to travel outside the city, where we reside, to try something new! The service was great and attentive from entrance through the whole experience. We love tapa style food and like the concept of tapa service. We ordered a total of 6 tapas. There wasn’t one of all six that was not overpowered with flavor. The starch to protein to flavor ratio was well off. This is constructive criticism that should be taken professionally. From one business owner to another, the concept is beautiful but almost all of the food was over powered with too much flavor to the point of it being un enjoyable. Entered with high expectations, left unsatisfied.

First time at Holmes. We had a good experience, and there is room for improvement. Two plates out of five I had I will recommend. The scallops and seared tuna. Table service was fine, but it could definitely improve with attention to detail. Nice addition to the area with room to grow. I will give it another try, once the menu has been updated for the season. Worth trying it.
Awesome atmosphere. Amazing drinks. Great food. Service is incredible

You order several small plates that are very expensive and don't have very much food on them.  They are pretty tasty but the flavor is definitely not worth the price and the avocado in one of the dishes I ordered tasted overly ripe and you could see the brown streaks in it, I thought for that price at least the food would be done perfectly.  I sat outside on the porch and the atmosphere was great and very relaxing, our server was wonderful.  I wouldn't recommend going here unless you just feel like blowing some money.  My boyfriend and I split 3 plates of food and were still hungry afterward.
The food was amazing, the staff was extremely friendly and went above and beyond.
Staff was great. Setting wonderful. Food was just OK.  I love small plate eating. But the choices were not my cup of tea. Would I go back? Maybe. But it would not be my first choice for sure.

Small plates done exceedingly well, fantastic craft cocktails, knowledgeable/friendly staff...all walking distance from home. We're familiar with Chef's solid work from the early days of St. Cecilia and are thrilled to have him so close to home!

Great menu selection. Great venue. Creative. Decor, food, dining experience all top of the line. You can definitely tell the chef knows what they’re doing. Highly recommend to any Alpharetta/Atlanta foodie who is looking for a unbelievable dining night out.

Wonderful first experience, from service and ambiance, to food quality and variety of options. None of the eight dishes we tried had the same taste profile, and none disappointed. Good-looking cocktail selection and wine list, too! This is definitely the new top favourite destination for me in the area.
Excellent service and well-crafted food.

Of course, Taylor delivers.... Tuna, scallops, bone marrow toast, and others were all delicious.  Cool atmosphere and friendly staff.  Will definitely go back and would definitely stand with you on a mountain.
Amazing food, amazing atmosphere, great for casual yet fine dining. Every plate was fantastic! Mouth watering, definitely coming back, and highly recommend!

Meh.  Mediocre. Overpriced.  Everything was oversalted. I've dined at enough small plates restaurants to know that if you charge what Holmes charges for dishes, they should be good enough that it makes up for the small portions.  This was not the case for Holmes, of the 4 small plates we ordered, 3 were grossly oversalted.  Only 1 dish had balanced flavours. The portions were microscopic (what can only be described as a couple of bites per each dish).  2 drinks and 4 dishes added up to a $79 (before tip) tab.  I should have known when, while waiting for our food to arrive, I asked the couple seated next to us "how is it"' and they replied tentatively "uh, it's interesting".  There are so many restaurants in this neighborhood to choose from.  I'd say, do yourself a favor and skip this place. We even tried to alert the restaurant of their mistakes, as we sent their carrot dish back telling the waitress that the carrots were inedible.  They were an overcooked amazingly over seasoned/salty mess. They brought us a replacement within a minute, with what tasted like the exact same carrots we had just asked to have redone.  We did this because even though the 2 other dishes we received were oversalted, they were at least "edible".  The carrots were the last straw.  We left hungry and perturbed by our experience.

We went there last night and sat outside on the patio. The food was DEEELISH! We had the cauliflower, potatoes (2 servings, so good!), steak, baby carrots, pork belly, heirloom tomato salad and it was all so good. This is a small plate restaurant so it can add up fast. They have their own herb garden in the back and the food was fresh and so flavorful. The ambiance and location were perfect!
Go check out the hottest new place in downtown Alpharetta!  Fabulous bar, food and service!

Amazing staff, drinks, and food. Sat at the bar and got amazing service from Sam and Adrienne,m. Highly recommend this place, they will make you a drink off the menu to your tastes! We got the potatoes, carrots,  and pork belly...simply amazing!
Great food!!! Fantastic atmosphere
